1. To change word size in python, 
    change    mem_param.word_size
    change    mem_param.frac_size

2. To change buffer number in python,
    change    mem_param.buffer_num


3. To change word size in rtl,
    change  header.vh: DATA_WIDTH
   
4. To change buffer number in rtl,
    change  header.vh: N_PE
 
The external_memory.sv will load the input.dat and model.dat file.
The start address of input.dat is manually coded in the sv file. This number is actually mem_param.ram_input_start
Start address of model.dat file is 0.

May need to change the 'scale' in RTL regfile if changing word sizes


ONE FLAW: the int2frac will convert 16bit float to 16 bits integer but only keep the LSB8 bits valid, so fracbits actually determines the precision


